  2. Map

    HashMap

    boolean .containsKey()
    boolean .containsValue() // O(n)
    int .size()
    void .put(k, v)
    V .get(k) // return null
    V .remove(k) // null returned if no such key.
    .clear()
    .isEmpty()
    Set<Map.Entry<K,V>> .entrySet()
    Set<Key> .keySet()

    loop 

                    Map<String, Object> map = ...;

                for (String key : map.keySet()) {
                    // ...
                }
                for (Map.Entry<String, Object> entry : map.entrySet()) {
                    String key = entry.getKey();
                    Object value = entry.getValue();
                    // ...
                }

  3. List

    LinkedList: Best for add, insert, delete O(1). ArrayList: Best for Get O(1), with initial size, add takes O(1)

    LinkedList

    boolean .contains(E)
    int .size()
    void .add(E)
    void .clear()
    boolean remove(E) // true if removed the first
    E .get(index) // throws IndexOutOfBound
    E .set(index, newE) // return the old E, throws IndexOutOfBound
    void .addFirst(E o);
    void .addLast(E o);
    E .getFirst();
    E .getLast();
    E .removeFirst();
    E .removeLast();
